
@prefix acl: <http://www.w3.org/ns/auth/acl#>.

### Access policies for the client (and owner) must be repeated in each nested ACL.

<#client>
    a acl:Authorization;
    acl:agent <https://use.id/projectron>;
    acl:accessTo <./>;
    acl:default <./>;
    acl:mode 
        acl:Read,
        acl:Write,
        acl:Append,
        acl:Delete,
        acl:Control.
    
<#owner>
    a acl:Authorization;
    acl:agent <https://use.id/alice>;
    acl:accessTo <./>;
    acl:default <./>;
    acl:mode 
        acl:Read.

### Access policies granted for the entire shape tree must also be repeated on an instance level.

<#3e8ebb79-b836-4ea6-a984-c8ee0d18231d>
    a acl:Authorization;
    acl:agent <https://use.id/bob>;
    acl:accessTo <./>;
    acl:default <./>;
    acl:mode 
        acl:Read,
        acl:Create.

### Additionally, access can be granted to third parties (e.g. Bob), in sync with the Access Needs.

<#3e8ebb79-b836-4ea6-a984-c8ee0d18231d>
    a acl:Authorization;
    acl:agent <https://use.id/cooper>;
    acl:accessTo <./>;
    acl:default <./>;
    acl:mode 
        acl:Read.